EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass legislation to increase penalties for physical assaults on the elderly.
EventItemMatterName: Increase penalties for physical assaults on the elderly.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Aging
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass A. 0697, which would amend the public authorities law, in relation to establishing a no fare program for transportation on the New York City Transit Authority system, the Long Island Rail Road, and the Metro-North Commuter Railroad Company for senior citizens.
EventItemMatterName: Establishing a no fare program for transportation on the NYCTA system, the Long Island Rail Road, and the Metro-North Commuter Railroad Company for senior citizens. (A.0697)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution endorsing the Speaker’s decision to join with the Administration in filing, on behalf of the Council, an amicus brief in support of the Plaintiffs in the litigation between individual tenants and landlords captioned Rosario v. Diagonal Realty LLC for the purpose of supporting Local Law 44 of 1993 amending the City’s J-51 tax abatement program to prohibit discrimination by landlords against tenants using or participating in government funded housing assistance programs including Section 8.
EventItemMatterName: Filing, on behalf of the Council, an amicus brief in support of the Plaintiffs in the litigation between individual tenants and landlords captioned Rosario v. Diagonal Realty LLC.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Contracts
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the charter of the city of New York to require notification to the Council of the city of New York of emergency procurements.
EventItemMatterName: NYC charter to require notification to the Council of the city of NY of emergency procurements.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Youth Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution commending the 10% For Youth Campaign for urging that budget surpluses  be used to guarantee summer jobs for every teen, a Beacon program for every neighborhood, and an expansion of dropout/pushout programs.
EventItemMatterName: Commending the 10% For Youth Campaign for urging that budget surpluses be used to guarantee summer jobs for every teen, a Beacon program for every neighborhood, and an expansion of dropout/pushout programs.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Mayor of the City of New York to use City employees rather than private consultants and contractors to provide City services that can be performed by City employees.
EventItemMatterName: Mayor of NYC  to use City employees rather than private consultants and contractors to provide City services that can be performed by City employees.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring any person who marks a street or sidewalk for the purpose of paving, maintaining or restoring said street or sidewalk to remove all such marks once the work is complete.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring any person who marks a street or sidewalk for the purpose of paving, maintaining or restoring said street or sidewalk to remove all such marks once the work is complete.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to creating criminal and civil penalties for damaging items of religious worship or religious articles that are contained on private property.
EventItemMatterName: Creating criminal and civil penalties for damaging items of religious worship or religious articles that are contained on private property.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to inspections by the department of buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Inspections by the department of buildings.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to an alternative enforcement program by the department of housing preservation and development for violations of the housing maintenance code and multiple dwelling law.
EventItemMatterName: Alternative enforcement program by the department of housing preservation and development for violations of the housing maintenance code and multiple dwelling law.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on Congress to reintroduce and pass the Second Chance Act of 2005, which would reauthorize a Department of Justice grant program that, among other things, facilitates the reentry of offenders into the community and establishes a task force on Federal programs and activities relating to the reentry of offenders into the community.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to reintroduce and pass the Second Chance Act of 2005.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to serial acts of public lewdness.
EventItemMatterName: Establishing certain penalties for the offense of public lewdness.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to amend the definition of drug, as used in the sections of the Vehicle and Traffic Law that relate to the offenses of operating a motor vehicle while under the influence of alcohol or drugs, to permit the arrest and charging under those sections of individuals under the influence of chemical compounds found in products that can be abused as inhalants.
EventItemMatterName: NYS Legislature to amend the definition of drug, as used in the sections of the Vehicle and Traffic Law.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Land Use
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Department of City Planning to file an application to amend the text of the Zoning Resolution in regard to creating R2-N, a contextual Residence District for areas with single-family homes on lots less than forty feet in width.
EventItemMatterName: Department of City Planning to file an application to amend the text of the Zoning Resolution in regard to creating R2-N.
